  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improved emergency housing of IDPs and returnees in Monguno and Ngala, Borno State, Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In support to the UN-led coordinated humanitarian response in Borno State, INTERSOS is proposing a 6-months project that will address the basic registration needs of the most vulnerable groups of IDPs in Monguno and Ngala Local Governments Area (LGA), Borno State, Nigeria. 
The project has been designed to meet the affected population&#x2019;s most urgent needs in a sustainable way that empowers local communities and service providers by working through existing structures where available, adhering to Nigerian guidelines and protocols, and empowering community stakeholders and other project&#x2019;s beneficiaries in direct service delivery. Focusing on the particular needs of women and children, elderly and disabled people, INTERSOS will target communities where service providers are currently unavailable or unable to cope with the overwhelming needs of returnees, IDPs and host community.
In the project focus area, INTERSOS will scale up its intervention with the provision of basic reception and hosting services to displaced population. INTERSOS will strive to fulfill the basic humanitarian needs of the most vulnerable communities through the provision of adequate temporary housing solutions and reception center facilities. With the assistance of other services providers, the project will enhance the different referral pathways and the referral mechanism.</narrative>
  </description>
